    <li id="fn:65" role="doc-endnote">
      <p>On this point, see Althusser‚Äôs long-neglected but essential
reformulation of the problem of Marx‚Äôs methodology in his 1977
preface to G√©rard Dum√©nil‚Äôs <em>Le concept de loi √©conomique dans ‚ÄúLe
Capital.‚Äù</em> The preface, translated by G. M. Goshgarian, appears in
<em>Rethinking Marxism</em> 30, no. 1 (2018): 4‚Äì24. While in this late text
Althusser develops a brilliant interpretation of Marx‚Äôs methodology
and the contingency of the latter‚Äôs analytical focus on valorization
in <em>Capital</em>, this arguably culminates in Althusser‚Äôs problematic
(not to say symptomatic) hypostatization of the categories ‚Äúuse value, labour productivity, and‚Äîclass struggle! [<em>sic</em>]‚Äù as
heterogeneous to, rather than constituted by, the logic and social
demands of valorization (20). For all its brilliance, in other
words, Althusser‚Äôs remains a critique from the standpoint of labor
rather than a critique of (capitalist) labor per se. See also Fabio
Bruschi, ‚ÄúSplitting Science: The Althusserian Interpretation of
